40|$|The {{purpose of}} the study have been: (1) to provide an explanatory, descriptive, and {{analytic}} viewpoint of the functions and structure of <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention</b> centers (2) to provide an intensive investigation of counseling and treatment practices in <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention</b> centers and (3) to relate the experiences that the writer has encountered as a resident counselor at Help House Inc. (twenty-four hour drug and <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention</b> center in Denton, Texas) to sociological, psychological, social psychological and philosophical constructs that deal with or pertain to <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention,</b> particularly in the area of drug use. The study indicates how participatory observation serves as an aid in acquiring insight into sociological areas such as <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention</b> centers. The role of the participatory observer is most important because concepts and theories arise out of actual situations...|$|R
