40|$|More {{often there}} are events {{occurring}} in society that leave {{children in a}} crisis state which affects them both emotionally and intellectually. School staff are prominent figures {{in the lives of}} children, and must be both prepared and knowledgeable in order to help during times of crisis. School Psychologists, in particular, are specifically trained in counseling and consultation necessary for effective <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention.</b> School Psychologists must be the leaders in creating and implementing <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention</b> plans in the schools. The following project contains a literature review of <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention,</b> and a detailed <b>crisis</b> <b>intervention</b> plan for a small, rural district in upstate New York...|$|R
